If you want to call an Oracle database function:

    CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION fn_count_comments ( 
        postId IN NUMBER ) 
        RETURN NUMBER 
    IS
        commentCount NUMBER; 
    BEGIN
        SELECT COUNT(*) INTO commentCount 
        FROM post_comment 
        WHERE post_id = postId; 
        RETURN( commentCount ); 
    END;

You can&#39;t use the `StoredProcedureQuery` since it does not work with Hibernate 5, so you can call it like this:

